WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.530 --> 00:00:03.130
&gt;&gt; Guy Lamolinara:
Good morning everyone.

00:00:03.130 --> 00:00:06.330
Thanks for coming to the
National Book Festival today.

00:00:06.330 --> 00:00:10.290
I'm Guy Lamolinara and I work
for the Library of Congress.

00:00:10.290 --> 00:00:13.710
All day here, at the Library of
Congress National Book Festival;

00:00:13.710 --> 00:00:16.240
we are recognizing and
celebrating the importance

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:18.920
of reading, and authors
and books.

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:22.200
The library makes it seem
easy to do every year,

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:25.250
but the truth is the National
Book Festival is a huge

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:29.870
undertaking, a huge financial
undertaking, but yet is free

00:00:29.870 --> 00:00:32.420
for everyone because
of the generous support

00:00:32.420 --> 00:00:34.860
from our sponsors
and supporters.

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:37.730
So, please spread the joy of
reading with your gift online

00:00:37.730 --> 00:00:41.940
if you can at loc.gov/donate
and you can do

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:45.890
that from the festival app or
when you purchase books today.

00:00:45.890 --> 00:00:49.190
Now onto the event that
you all are here for.

00:00:49.190 --> 00:00:52.160
Before I begin, I want to
thank Pizza Hut BOOK IT!

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:55.330
Program for sponsoring
Kate DiCamillo

00:00:55.330 --> 00:00:59.340
and Harry Bliss's presentation
today, and I also need

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:03.010
to tell you we are recording
this for later broadcasting

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:04.310
and if you have not already,

00:01:04.310 --> 00:01:06.450
could you please
silence your cellphones.

00:01:06.450 --> 00:01:08.410
Thank you.

00:01:08.410 --> 00:01:11.280
Kate DiCamillo is the
beloved author of many books

00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:14.460
for children including
"Flora Ulysses",

00:01:14.460 --> 00:01:15.790
"The Tale of Despereaux",

00:01:15.790 --> 00:01:18.490
both of which received
Newbery Medals.

00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:20.500
Her most recent middle
grade novel,

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:23.890
"Raymie Nightingale" was an
instant number one New York

00:01:23.890 --> 00:01:28.060
Times Best Seller and a
National Book Award finalist.

00:01:28.060 --> 00:01:30.440
She is also the author
of "Because

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:33.030
of Winn Dixie" a
Newbery Honor book,

00:01:33.030 --> 00:01:36.450
"The Tiger Rising" a
National Book Award finalist,

00:01:36.450 --> 00:01:37.870
"The Miraculous Journey

00:01:37.870 --> 00:01:42.040
of Edward Tulane" a number
one New York Times Best Seller

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:43.940
and "Mercy Watson" the series

00:01:43.940 --> 00:01:47.050
which is illustrated
by Chris Van Dusen.

00:01:47.050 --> 00:01:50.190
Kate is also a former
National Ambassador

00:01:50.190 --> 00:01:53.530
for Young People's Literature
for the Library of Congress

00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:55.700
and she has more than
twenty-two million books

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:57.640
in print nationwide.

00:01:57.640 --> 00:01:59.890
Kate lives in Minneapolis

00:01:59.890 --> 00:02:04.770
where she faithfully writes two
pages a day five days a week.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:08.390
I've personally been lucky to
know Kate for several years

00:02:08.390 --> 00:02:11.240
and I can tell you as you
would suspect that she is one

00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:14.180
of the nicest people
you could ever meet.

00:02:14.180 --> 00:02:17.990
I can also tell you Kate
has the world's best laugh.

00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:20.350
So what you want to
do is make Kate laugh

00:02:20.350 --> 00:02:22.630
and you will not
be disappointed.

00:02:22.630 --> 00:02:27.360
The work of Harry Bliss is
very familiar to anybody

00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:29.540
who reads the New
Yorker magazine.

00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:33.190
He is both a cartoonist and
cover artist for the magazine

00:02:33.190 --> 00:02:37.030
and he had drawn more than
fifteen New Yorker covers.

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:40.350
Harry has illustrated many
picture books including the

00:02:40.350 --> 00:02:43.310
number one New York
Times bestselling series

00:02:43.310 --> 00:02:47.470
by Doreen Cronin that began
with "Diary of a Worm"

00:02:47.470 --> 00:02:48.770
and is he is both written

00:02:48.770 --> 00:02:53.080
and illustrated several picture
books including "Grace for Gus"

00:02:53.080 --> 00:02:55.090
and "Luke on the Loose."

00:02:55.090 --> 00:02:57.960
I can tell you that Harry
loves meeting his fans.

00:02:57.960 --> 00:03:01.620
He visits many schools across
the country and he interacts

00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:03.180
with thousands of children all

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:07.250
over the world teaching
comics, drawing and satire.

00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:11.280
He and Kate have collaborated
on their book "Good Rosie!"

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:15.510
Please welcome Kate
DiCamillo and Harry Bliss.

00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:21.100
[ Applause ]

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:22.640
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: So,
how are you all doing?

