We'll show you, well
let's just do a,

00:04:06.830 --> 00:04:08.250
we'll show you a
little bit about what

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:14.230
"Good Rosie" is about, and
typically when an author

00:04:14.230 --> 00:04:17.920
and illustrator do books
together you don't do

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:19.470
them together.

00:04:19.470 --> 00:04:21.860
Usually the publisher
decides who's going

00:04:21.860 --> 00:04:23.900
to illustrate a book, but Harry

00:04:23.900 --> 00:04:26.340
and I had done a book together
before and we had also,

00:04:26.340 --> 00:04:28.660
Harry had illustrated a
poem that I had written

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:31.940
that had a dog in
it and we had wanted

00:04:31.940 --> 00:04:33.980
for a longtime to do a dog book.

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:37.950
So, we collab; we decided that
we were going to do this book

00:04:37.950 --> 00:04:41.280
and it is; how many
of you all have dogs?

00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:42.580
That's excellent.

00:04:42.580 --> 00:04:45.380
How many have cats?

00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:50.820
Okay. So, Harry and
I are dog people.

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:55.720
So, this is just the story of
a dog who meets some other dogs

00:04:55.720 --> 00:05:00.300
at a dog park and not a lot
happens, but a lot happens.

00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:03.720
So, Harry do you want to take
it from there for a minute?

00:05:03.720 --> 00:05:05.020
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah,
with the book?

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:06.320
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Yeah with the book.

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:07.620
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:05:07.620 --> 00:05:08.920
I love dogs.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:12.160
I love all animals, but in
particular, I'm fifty-four

00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:13.460
and something happened.

00:05:13.460 --> 00:05:14.840
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
I'm fifty-four too.

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:16.140
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:17.440
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:18.740
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: You Pisces?

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:20.040
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
I'm an Aries.

00:05:20.040 --> 00:05:21.340
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Oh, okay.

00:05:21.340 --> 00:05:22.640
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Yeah, yeah.

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:25.050
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: So, yeah
this is serendipitous

00:05:25.050 --> 00:05:26.350
that this book came about.

00:05:26.350 --> 00:05:31.310
So, this is George and
Rosie lives with George.

00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:32.610
Rosie is a good dog.

00:05:32.610 --> 00:05:33.910
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Yeah.

00:05:33.910 --> 00:05:35.210
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: You're
supposed to read this, right?

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:36.510
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Oh, should I read it?

00:05:36.510 --> 00:05:37.810
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah, well
let's go to the next one.

00:05:37.810 --> 00:05:39.110
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Oh.

00:05:39.110 --> 00:05:41.690
Oh, Harry isn't that
beautiful art I have to say?

00:05:41.690 --> 00:05:45.010
I mean, it's just like don't
you want to pick her up?"

00:05:45.010 --> 00:05:46.310
[ Applause ]

00:05:46.310 --> 00:05:47.610
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Thank you.

00:05:47.610 --> 00:05:50.290
Well, I chose, I chose to do
this in comic sequential panels

00:05:50.290 --> 00:05:54.310
because I'm a cartoonist and I
love panels and I love the fact

00:05:54.310 --> 00:05:57.630
that you can, the time, the
space between the panels it's

00:05:57.630 --> 00:06:01.570
like a little beat in music
like a rest if you will, so.

00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:05.330
So, there's Rosie and
she lives with George

00:06:05.330 --> 00:06:06.950
and Rosie's a lonely dog.

00:06:06.950 --> 00:06:08.250
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Right.

00:06:08.250 --> 00:06:09.550
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:06:09.550 --> 00:06:10.850
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
She's lonely.

00:06:10.850 --> 00:06:12.150
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:13.450
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: She
feels a certain melancholy

00:06:13.450 --> 00:06:15.840
which is a word that shows up
in a lot of my stuff actually.

00:06:15.840 --> 00:06:17.270
But let's not think about that.

00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:18.570
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Let's
not talk about that.

00:06:18.570 --> 00:06:19.870
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Yeah, okay alright.

00:06:19.870 --> 00:06:21.170
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: But
it's a good work though.

00:06:21.170 --> 00:06:22.470
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Yeah, yeah.

00:06:22.470 --> 00:06:23.770
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: It is.

00:06:23.770 --> 00:06:25.070
Rosie and George walk together

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:26.510
and sometimes Rosie
chases squirrels.

00:06:26.510 --> 00:06:29.370
She runs very fast,
as fast as she can,

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:31.350
but she never catches anything.

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:33.720
You want to do George?

00:06:33.720 --> 00:06:35.600
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Rosie
always returns to George.

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:38.560
I've been a good
dog Rosie, good dog.

00:06:38.560 --> 00:06:40.670
But I can't see that part
over there where George.

00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:41.970
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:06:41.970 --> 00:06:43.270
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Talks
about the clouds, yeah.

00:06:43.270 --> 00:06:44.570
What does it say?

00:06:44.570 --> 00:06:45.870
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Well, he's "Look

00:06:45.870 --> 00:06:48.660
at the clouds Rosie
aren't they magnificent?"

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:51.540
"That one looks like
Abraham Lincoln."

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:53.370
George thinks that the clouds,

00:06:53.370 --> 00:06:55.240
that most clouds
look like presidents.

00:06:55.240 --> 00:07:00.060
Rosie thinks that most
clouds look like squirrels.

00:07:00.060 --> 00:07:03.850
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: One day
George sees something different

00:07:03.850 --> 00:07:06.180
in the clouds.

00:07:06.180 --> 00:07:07.480
Say it.

00:07:07.480 --> 00:07:08.780
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: "Look Rosie!

00:07:08.780 --> 00:07:11.260
That one looks like a dog!"

00:07:11.260 --> 00:07:13.060
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: "The
cloud does look like a dog."

00:07:13.060 --> 00:07:15.700
Rosie wags her tail,
"Hello, hello!"

00:07:15.700 --> 00:07:17.000
she shouts.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.300
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: "Woof-woof."

00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:19.850
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: The dog
cloud does not answer her.

00:07:19.850 --> 00:07:23.950
Rosie feels lonely in an
empty bowel sort of way.

00:07:23.950 --> 00:07:25.960
George looks down at Rosie.

00:07:25.960 --> 00:07:27.630
He looks up at the cloud.

00:07:27.630 --> 00:07:28.930
"Hmm."

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:30.230
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Hmm.

00:07:30.230 --> 00:07:32.120
"I've got an idea Rosie.

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:33.930
Let's try something new."

00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:35.750
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: And
something new is going

00:07:35.750 --> 00:07:38.890
to be the dog park which is
where all the action begins.

00:07:38.890 --> 00:07:42.810
Can you flip forward so we
can see some of who she meets?

00:07:42.810 --> 00:07:44.300
This is Maurice.

00:07:44.300 --> 00:07:47.290
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah,
she meets Maurice.

00:07:47.290 --> 00:07:48.590
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: [Brief
laughter] It doesn't go well

00:07:48.590 --> 00:07:54.150
at first and then can you
flip until we see Fifi?"

00:07:54.150 --> 00:07:55.450
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Fifi
comes along.

00:07:55.450 --> 00:07:56.750
There's Fifi.

00:07:56.750 --> 00:07:58.050
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: Yeah.

00:07:58.050 --> 00:07:59.350
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: "Yip-yip."

00:07:59.350 --> 00:08:00.650
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Yeah, there's Fifi, yeah.

00:08:00.650 --> 00:08:05.640
And with both of these dogs
it doesn't go well at first,

00:08:05.640 --> 00:08:08.830
but they [brief laughter], they
figure out how to be friends.

00:08:08.830 --> 00:08:11.160
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: After
some real drama.

00:08:11.160 --> 00:08:12.460
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Yeah, after some drama.

00:08:12.460 --> 00:08:13.760
So.

00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:15.060
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: You know.

00:08:15.060 --> 00:08:16.360
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: That's one

00:08:16.360 --> 00:08:18.300
of my favorite panels,
"Drop it!"

00:08:18.300 --> 00:08:19.600
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah.

00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:20.900
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: "Drop it!"

00:08:20.900 --> 00:08:22.200
Yeah.

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:23.500
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Dogs being dogs.

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:24.930
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo: And that's
Fifi's tail hanging out there.

00:08:24.930 --> 00:08:27.770
Yeah. But we won't, we won't
tell you all what happens,

00:08:27.770 --> 00:08:31.830
but there is a little bit drama
and everything turns out okay.

00:08:31.830 --> 00:08:37.370
But let's, let's see if you
guys want to ask questions

00:08:37.370 --> 00:08:39.330
and then let's have
Harry do the art.

00:08:39.330 --> 00:08:40.630
&gt;&gt; Harry Bliss: Yeah, yeah.

00:08:40.630 --> 00:08:41.930
&gt;&gt; Kate DiCamilllo:
Do you think?

00:08:41.930 --> 00:08:43.230
Because we can't.

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:44.530
Yes.

