00:09:39.730 --> 00:09:41.030
What inspired me to write

00:09:41.030 --> 00:09:43.000
"Because Winn-Dixie" is
a good question for now

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:49.390
because I had moved from
Florida to Minneapolis

00:09:49.390 --> 00:09:53.910
and it was the first time in my
life I had been without a dog

00:09:53.910 --> 00:09:56.500
and we know how many of you all
have dogs and also that some

00:09:56.500 --> 00:10:00.800
of you have cats, but I just
could not, I could not get

00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:02.360
over the fact that
I didn't have a dog.

00:10:02.360 --> 00:10:04.890
I couldn't have one in the
apartment where I lived,

00:10:04.890 --> 00:10:09.210
and also it was a brutal
winter in Minnesota

00:10:09.210 --> 00:10:11.480
and I was homesick for Florida.

00:10:11.480 --> 00:10:14.230
So, Winn-Dixie takes
place in Florida

00:10:14.230 --> 00:10:17.990
and Winn-Dixie is
centered around a dog.

00:10:17.990 --> 00:10:21.850
I could not have a dog, but
this is the beauty of writing

00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.740
and of creating things.

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:28.330
I could make-up the best
dog that I could imagine

00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:31.180
which was Winn-Dixie
the biggest, smelliest,

00:10:31.180 --> 00:10:33.990
smilingest dog in the
world, so that's--

00:10:33.990 --> 00:10:36.770
that's where that came from.

00:10:36.770 --> 00:10:40.910
Yes, yes I see you.

00:10:40.910 --> 00:10:43.050
&gt;&gt; Hi Kate, it's
lovely to see you.

00:10:43.050 --> 00:10:45.360
Winn-Dixie was far and
away our daughters,

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:47.090
three daughters favorite
book of all-time,

00:10:47.090 --> 00:10:48.740
so we do have a favorite.

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:51.740
I'm asking you, did you
have a Jack Russell in mind

00:10:51.740 --> 00:10:53.710
when you wrote the story?

